post_text:
This is for the JGTC in honor of getting back on the stage and our first company meeting of 2020-21!!

🎶Can't you feel a brand new day!🎶
shared_text:
James Alonzo White
September 1 at 12:05 PM ·

If anyone knows me, they know I love THE WIZ! It would be a dream to choreograph and/or dance for a Wiz on Broadway lol. So for my birthday I decided to put together a short video, recreating one of my favorite scenes from the movie: A BRAND NEW DAY! We all know these last few months have been filled with a lot of darks days and moments, so here is a little light to shine in those dark corners! Also s/o to this amazing cast of dancers! They are truly the embodiment of talent! ❤️❤️

👣: Me
📹: @allyvisuals

Dancers:
Robby G. Boyer Mary-Angela Granberry Shayna Wheatley Cedric Greene Nerita NV McFarlane James Luc Keisha 'Sparkle' Hughes Robyn Williams Chantel Renee Coral Dolphin Kiana King Ryan Miller Shane Fowler Craig D Washington Dobbin Pinkney Alexis Tillman Arden Silvers Harris Jay Mills Kendrick Samuel Jason F.C. Laws

#thewiz #brandnewday #choreography #musicaltheatre #virgoseason #blackgirlmagic #blackboyjoy #melanin #blacklivesmatter

post_text:
The ghost light was created as a tool to keep us safe (from falling off the stage), it has since evolved into a metaphor for theatre’s ability to be light in the darkness.

We will draw the curtain temporarily on our spring production. But we will return to shine more brightly then ever. The show must and will go on.

The John Glenn Theatre Company will be presenting its spring musical in just a few weeks. Please retain your tickets as they will be honored for the same day and time. We thank you for your support.

post_text: Don't miss the Purdue Glee Club!! One of our very own John Glenn Theatre Company members will be performing!!
shared_text:
John Glenn Music Department
January 24 at 6:07 PM ·

Don’t miss this! The Purdue Varsity Glee Club will be at John Glenn High School on Sunday, February 2nd, at 2:00 p. m. Join us as we support John Glenn alumn and Purdue senior member Bryce Lemert. The John Glenn Advanced Choirs have been invited to join the men of Purdue in singing Peter Wilhousky’s Battle Hymn of the Republic. We are very proud to welcome the men of Purdue and to present this internationally recognized choir to our community. Tickets are $20 for adults and $15 for students. To reserve tickets please call or text Sharon Lemert at 574-210-6124.

post_text: The John Glenn Theatre Company has lost another of its assets. Lloyd Meyer shared his talents with the theatre company for over 20 years. Whether building the inventors machine for Beauty and the Beast or the milk car for Tevye in Fiddler on the Roof, if it had wheels Lloyd was our man. Lloyd was also the best audience member for a dress rehearsal as his laughter could be heard throughout the auditorium. If Lloyd laughed, you knew you nailed the joke. Lloyd was a true friend for the theatre and will be greatly missed by all.

post_text:
Professor Plum/Luke Lemert – an x-psychiatrist with a huge ego and a shady past. Now he works for the government which is not much different. If I were you I’d be careful around this smooth operator. Cunning yet suspicious, don’t let your guard down around him.

Luke Lemert is a senior at John Glenn. In 2018 he portrayed Enjolras in last year’s production of Les Miserables Luke has been a member of the John Glenn Theatre Co. since his 8th grade year when he was part of the company of The Music Man. Luke also plays football and is a member of Rhythm Express.

Miss Scarlet/Kayla Kerchove - a notorious Washington D.C. madam knows all there is to know, you know?? Ruthless and cunning, she has the dirt on everyone. Without a doubt Miss Scarlet is not a lady to be trifled with. I'd keep the lights on when she’s around if I were you...

Kayla is a senior and this is her fourth year on stage for the John Glenn Theatre Co. She was most recently seen dancing (badly) in You Can’t It With You and singing in Les Miserable as Cosette. Kayla also performs in the Rhythm Express show choir. Not only is she a fine actress, but can also build the set!!

post_text:
Wadsworth/Sam Carson – You’re typical English butler in a not so typical place, Boddy Manor. Wadsworth tries his best to keep a tidy house with all the evenings’ guests arriving for mysterious dinner party Will he be able to hold it together or will the pressure final make him crack? Ring the doorbell and join the party and find out for yourself!!

Sam made his first appearance on the John Glenn stage as a little gorilla in Tarzan! A few years later as an 8th grader he was Tommy Giles in The Music Man. Sam has been a company asset both on and off the stage. Sam also plays football for the Falcons and has been in Rhythm Express for the past 3 years.

John Glenn Theatre Company presents Clue on Stage November 22, 23 and 24th. Tickets are $10 at the door for general seating. Doors open 30 minutes before curtain.

Sam has been a company asset both on and off the stage. Sam also plays football for the Falcons and has been in Rhythm Express for the past 3 years.

post_text:
Tonight something special happened...I literally watched my LES MISERABLES cast transform from high school students in 2019 to French citizens in 1832. It happened in front of my eyes and AFTER I had a “one-sided conversation” with them (Fansler Kids-it was only about a “5”, but they weren’t expecting it😜). We had a much more focused rehearsal after that and I saw and heard continued improvement and we still have a week to go! I think we are creating something exciting and the work is paying off! (They just occasionally need to be reminded of my existence in the darkened auditorium!)
I hope they know how proud of their hard work I really am!🎭👍❤️😎

Tickets go on sale on Monday beginning at 11:00 am in the high school and will be sold from 11:00-7:00 each day and then before each performance—-March 8-7:30; March 9-2:00 and 7:30; and March 10-2:00. All seats are $10.00.

Make plans to attend- you won’t regret it!🎶🎭🎶🎭🎭🎶

post_text:
Soooo...I want to thank everyone, especially the students, for the very nice reception as I have returned to the Theatre Company. I am happy to be directing this group in You Can’t Take It With You and know you are going to enjoy it!
I am also excited to announce that we have received and submitted the contract to do a brand new show for the Theatre Company; one I have wanted to do for a long time....so barring any unexpected problems....we will be doing LES MISERABLES School Edition for our spring musical!!!
Big excitement for us and lots to do, but Connie and I are jumping back in with both feet!
Best wishes also to Mr. Snyder and to Mr. Dollins on their new jobs and a welcome to Mrs. Hostetler to the choir position.
We will keep you up to date!
